dbSanitize()

Description
    mixed dbSanitize(mixed $var [, bool $quotes = FALSE])
	Returns a cleaned variable for insertion into a MySQL database.
	
Parameters
    var
		The data to be sanitized.
	quotes
		Whether or not to add quotations to a string value passed to the function.
	
Return Values
    Returns the parameter, $var, in a sanitized form.
	
Examples
   <?php
		...
		// Get clean $_POST
		if(isset($_POST)) {
			foreach ($_POST as $key => $value) {
				$cleanKey                            = htmlSanitize($key);
				$this->cleanPost['HTML'][$cleanKey]  = htmlSanitize($value);
				$this->cleanPost['MYSQL'][$cleanKey] = dbSanitize($value);
				$this->cleanPost['RAW'][$cleanKey]   = $value;
			}
		...
	?>
	
See Also
	htmlSanitize()